### VS Code REST Client compatible examples
@base = http://127.0.0.1:8787
@token = {{login.response.body.$.token}}

### Register
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "stud2@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "full_name": "Student Two"
}

### Login
# @name login
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "stud2@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### Get Self User (replace 2 with returned id)
GET {{base}}/users/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List Users (admin token required)
GET {{base}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Upload Certificate (replace user_id)
POST {{base}}/certificates/upload?user_id=2&title=English%20Cert
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample.pdf

### List Certificates
GET {{base}}/users/2/certificates
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
